Generally viewed as a well-governed country since its independence from South Africa in 1990, Hopwood, the Institute's Excutive Director, says some of the country's laws have shielded public servants from prosecution, and have resulted in loopholes around ethical state practices. 

He was speaking at a round-table discussion in Johannesburg hosted by the South African Institute of International Affairs. 

